    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="453"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6111/1226: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-26">October 26,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received October 27—1:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1734. Personal for Soviet Ambassador. Have just read digest reported here on your
                    radio address October 21st.<note n="8" xml:id="d453fn8">The text of the radio
                        address by Ambassador Gromyko is printed in the <hi rend="italic">New York
                            Times</hi>, October 22, 1943, p. 10, col. 2.</note> It is an important
                    contribution toward establishment of mutual understanding and friendship between
                    the people of our two countries. May I send you my congratulations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
